{"type":"message","id":"39a3d9dd","parentId":"f94fce58","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:07:17.801Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 14:07 GMT+2] TELEGRAM MENU UPGRADE (Pro Stream).\n\n1.  **Analyze OpenClaw Commands:**\n    *   Read `openclaw.json` (commands section) or `src/bot/handlers.py` (if custom bot).\n    *   *Constraint:* OpenClaw native commands (`/new`, `/status`) are handled by the Gateway. We need to register *custom* commands for the DMarket bot.\n    *   *Action:* If using `python-telegram-bot` in `src/main.py`, update `set_my_commands`.\n\n2.  **Implement DMarket Commands (`src/main.py`):**\n    *   `/dm_start` -> Calls `agent_wrapper.py /start_bot`.\n    *   `/dm_stop` -> Calls `agent_wrapper.py /stop_bot`.\n    *   `/dm_status` -> Reads `bot.pid`, `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` (version), `docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md` (last change), and active LangFuse traces.\n    *   `/dm_dashboard` -> Returns current Streamlit URL.\n\n3.  **Menu Visuals (Description):**\n    *   `/dm_start` - \"🚀 Start DMarket HFT (High-Frequency)\"\n    *   `/dm_stop` - \"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"\n    *   `/dm_status` - \"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\n    *   `/dm_dashboard` - \"📈 Open Control Panel\"\n\n4.  **Conflict Resolution:**\n    *   Ensure native OpenClaw commands (`/clear` -> `/new`) are not overwritten.\n    *   Remove legacy handlers (Waxpeer).\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Updated `src/main.py` snippet.\n    *   Confirmation of menu registration.\n    *   Test output of `/dm_status` logic."}],"timestamp":1771157237799}}
{"type":"message","id":"7bf6b7ca","parentId":"39a3d9dd","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:07:23.308Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating Telegram Menu Upgrade**\n\nI'm currently focused on the Telegram menu upgrade for the \"DMarket HFT\" bot. I've begun to dissect the existing command structures, which seem to be defined within `openclaw.json` or potentially in `src/bot/handlers.py` and `src/main.py`. My next task is to implement the custom commands such as `/dm_start` and `/dm_`. I plan to integrate these using the current command framework.\n\n\n**Implementing Bot Command Logic**\n\nI'm now diving into the implementation phase. I've pinpointed `src/bot/handlers.py` as the primary location for handling the custom commands. My focus is on writing the command logic for `/dm_start`, `/dm_stop`, `/dm_status`, and `/dm_dashboard` within that file, ensuring proper error handling and response formatting. After that, I will tackle registration.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771157243128_552","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -F src/"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157243128_553","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157243305_554","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"openclaw.json"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":5275,"output":149,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5424,"cost":{"input":0.01055,"output":0.001788,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012338}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157237801}}
