{"type":"message","id":"4cb060c3","parentId":"3a9e841f","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:07:56.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Architecture Design**\n\nI've examined `src/core/engine.py`, identifying it as the heart of the trading logic. My focus has shifted towards the Telegram Bot's role, deciding `src/main.py` will serve as the controller. Furthermore, I've confirmed that the bot will initiate the process by executing `agent_wrapper.py /start_bot`.\n\n\n**Revising Execution Flow**\n\nI've re-evaluated the execution flow. I'm now clear that the trading logic resides in `src/core/engine.py`. The Telegram bot, controlled by `src/main.py`, will trigger the process. I'll need to update `agent_wrapper.py` to correctly launch the core trading component. I'm moving away from creating a new script like `src/trading_bot.py`; I think `agent_wrapper.py` itself is where the trading bot will be, and it should run the `engine.py`. I'm now inspecting `src/core/engine.py` to understand its functionalities better.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157276719_559","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/engine.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":8565,"output":222,"cacheRead":7883,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8787,"cost":{"input":0.01713,"output":0.002664,"cacheRead":0.0015766,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0213706}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157271379}}
{"type":"message","id":"feb898fd","parentId":"4cb060c3","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:07:56.745Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771157276719_559","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import asyncio\r\nimport logging\r\nimport traceback\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\nimport aiofiles\r\n\r\n# Conceptual integration for LOG agent\r\nLOG_AGENT_FILE = \"ERROR_LOG.md\"\r\n\r\nclass HybridEngine:\r\n    def __init__(self, dmarket_api, waxpeer_api):\r\n        self.dm = dmarket_api\r\n        self.wp = waxpeer_api\r\n        self.running = False\r\n\r\n    async def run(self):\r\n        self.running = True\r\n        logging.info(\"Engine started.\")\r\n        while self.running:\r\n            try:\r\n                # Main trading loop logic here (placeholder)\r\n                await asyncio.sleep(1)\r\n            except Exception as e:\r\n                # Use async error handling\r\n                await self.handle_error(e)\r\n                # Pause execution instead of immediate retry\r\n                await asyncio.sleep(10) \r\n\r\n    async def handle_error(self, e):\r\n        \"\"\"Async error logging to prevent blocking the event loop.\"\"\"\r\n        error_msg = traceback.format_exc()\r\n        \r\n        # Async Log for Console/File via aiofiles (Replacing blocking logging calls)\r\n        try:\r\n            async with aiofiles.open(\"engine.log\", \"a\") as f:\r\n                 await f.write(f\"[{datetime.now()}] CRITICAL ERROR: {e}\\n\")\r\n\r\n            async with aiofiles.open(LOG_AGENT_FILE, \"a\") as f:\r\n                await f.write(f\"\\n## ERROR REPORT - {datetime.now()}\\n\")\r\n                await f.write(f\"Type: {type(e).__name__}\\n\")\r\n                await f.write(f\"Details: {str(e)}\\n\")\r\n                await f.write(f\"Traceback:\\n```\\n{error_msg}\\n```\\n\")\r\n                await f.write(\"**ACTION REQUIRED:** LOG Agent (System Diagnostician) - Analyze and prescribe fix.\\n\")\r\n        except Exception as log_err:\r\n             # Fallback to print if async logging fails entirely\r\n             print(f\"Failed to write error log asynchronously: {log_err}\")\r\n        \r\n        # Notify about pause\r\n        try:\r\n            async with aiofiles.open(\"engine.log\", \"a\") as f:\r\n                await f.write(f\"[{datetime.now()}] Error logged for LOG agent analysis. Pausing main loop.\\n\")\r\n        except:\r\n            pass\r\n\r\n    def stop(self):\r\n        self.running = False\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771157276742}}
