{"type":"message","id":"57ee2b5a","parentId":"c9fa0a90","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:09:22.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Verifying File Existence**\n\nI've confirmed the existence of the critical documentation files, specifically `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` and `EVOLUTION_LOG.md`, within the `docs_archive` directory. This is a crucial step towards implementing the bot's core functionality, enabling it to access and utilize the protocol and evolution log for its operations.\n\n\n**Constructing Main Script**\n\nI'm now diving into the creation of `src/main.py`. I'll be using `python-telegram-bot` and the `ApplicationBuilder`. The script will handle commands like `/dm_start`, `/dm_stop`, `/dm_status`, and `/dm_dashboard`. I'm also incorporating logging and pulling the Telegram token from the environment variables.\n\n\n**Outlining Command Handlers**\n\nI'm now focusing on defining the command handlers within `src/main.py`. `/dm_start` will trigger `agent_wrapper.py /start_bot`, and `/dm_stop` will execute `agent_wrapper.py /stop_bot`. I will also work on `/dm_status`, where I'll read the PID file, and display content from the protocol and evolution log. I'll need to decide on error handling and how to provide feedback to the user.\n\n\n**Constructing Command Logic**\n\nI'm now building out the core command handlers in `src/main.py`. I'll use `subprocess.run` to call `agent_wrapper.py` for `/dm_start` and `/dm_stop`. For `/dm_status`, I'll read the PID file to check bot status, and extract relevant information from `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` (likely a version string) and the last change from `EVOLUTION_LOG.md`. I'll also add a `/dm_dashboard` command, which will return a placeholder URL for now. I've started the structure in the provided code.\n\n\n**Creating Basic Bot Script**\n\nI'm now building `src/main.py` using `python-telegram-bot`. I've verified the required files, `/dm_start` and `/dm_stop` commands will execute `agent_wrapper.py` using `subprocess.run`, and `/dm_status` will parse `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` (looking for a version) and the last line of `EVOLUTION_LOG.md`. I will also add a placeholder for `/dm_dashboard` which will return a URL. I'm handling the bot token via environment variables and integrating logging.\n\n\n**Writing Core Logic**\n\nI'm now implementing the core commands in `src/main.py`. I've verified the required files, `/dm_start` uses `subprocess.run` to call `agent_wrapper.py`, and `/dm_stop` does the same. `/dm_status` will parse `MASTER_PROTOCOL.md` and the last line of `EVOLUTION_LOG.md`. The `/dm_dashboard` command will return a URL, and I've integrated logging and environment variables for the bot token. I'll add error handling. The `sys.executable` usage looks right.\n\n\n**Developing Main Script**\n\nI'm now writing `src/main.py` with command handlers. The script confirms file existence, defines `/dm_start`, `/dm_stop`, `/dm_status`, and `/dm_dashboard` commands. `/dm_start` and `/dm_stop` call `agent_wrapper.py`. `/dm_status` reads the protocol and log files, including version checks. `/dm_dashboard` presents a placeholder URL. I will add error handling and assumed the `python-telegram-bot` version is recent. The correct pathing is also set.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771157362318_570","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\nfrom telegram import Update, BotCommand\nfrom telegram.ext import ApplicationBuilder, ContextTypes, CommandHandler\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    level=logging.INFO\n)\n\n# Paths (Assuming run from workspace root)\nAGENT_WRAPPER = \"src/agent_wrapper.py\"\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nMASTER_PROTOCOL = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nEVOLUTION_LOG = \"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md\"\n\n# Token from Env\nTOKEN = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n\nasync def dm_start(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🚀 Start DMarket HFT (High-Frequency)\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🚀 Starting DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        # Run agent_wrapper from root\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/start_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        # Format output\n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to start bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_stop(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🛑 Stopping DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/stop_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to stop bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    status_msg = \"📊 **Bot Status Report**\\n\\n\"\n    \n    # 1. PID / Running State\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                pid = f.read().strip()\n            status_msg += f\"✅ **Status:** Active (PID: {pid})\\n\"\n        except:\n            status_msg += \"⚠️ **Status:** PID file error\\n\"\n    else:\n        status_msg += \"💤 **Status:** Inactive (No PID file)\\n\"\n\n    # 2. Master Protocol Version\n    version = \"Unknown\"\n    if os.path.exists(MASTER_PROTOCOL):\n        try:\n            with open(MASTER_PROTOCOL, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                # Look for Title or Version line\n                content = f.read()\n                lines = content.splitlines()\n                for line in lines:\n                    if \"Version\" in line or \"v.\" in line.lower():\n                        version = line.strip()\n                        break\n                if version == \"Unknown\" and lines:\n                     version = lines[0].strip()\n        except Exception as e:\n             version = f\"Error: {e}\"\n    status_msg += f\"📜 **Protocol:** {version}\\n\"\n\n    # 3. Evolution Log (Last Change)\n    last_change = \"None\"\n    if os.path.exists(EVOLUTION_LOG):\n        try:\n             with open(EVOLUTION_LOG, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                lines = f.readlines()\n                # Get last non-empty line\n                for line in reversed(lines):\n                    if line.strip():\n                        last_change = line.strip()\n                        break\n        except:\n            pass\n    status_msg += f\"🧬 **Last Evolution:** {last_change}\\n\"\n    \n    # 4. LangFuse (Placeholder)\n    status_msg += \"🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\\n\"\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg, parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def dm_dashboard(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📈 Open Control Panel\"\"\"\n    # Assuming local streamlit or configured URL\n    url = os.getenv(\"STREAMLIT_URL\", \"http://localhost:8501\")\n    await update.message.reply_text(f\"📈 **Control Panel:** [Open Dashboard]({url})\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def post_init(application):\n    \"\"\"Set up commands on bot startup\"\"\"\n    commands = [\n        BotCommand(\"dm_start\", \"🚀 Start DMarket HFT\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_stop\", \"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_status\", \"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_dashboard\", \"📈 Open Control Panel\"),\n    ]\n    await application.bot.set_my_commands(commands)\n    logging.info(\"Commands registered with Telegram.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    if not TOKEN:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not set. Please set it in your environment.\")\n        # For testing purposes, we might want to exit gracefully or mock it, \n        # but for a real deployment, we exit.\n        sys.exit(1)\n        \n    application = ApplicationBuilder().token(TOKEN).post_init(post_init).build()\n    \n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_start', dm_start))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_stop', dm_stop))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_status', dm_status))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_dashboard', dm_dashboard))\n    \n    print(\"Telegram Bot Control Interface Started.\")\n    application.run_polling()\n","file_path":"src/main.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":16805,"output":3571,"cacheRead":15663,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20376,"cost":{"input":0.03361,"output":0.042852,"cacheRead":0.0031326,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0795946}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157333205}}
