{"type":"message","id":"8996ab3b","parentId":"04efd83a","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:09:28.300Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Revisiting Agent Wrapper**\n\nI've just been reviewing `src/agent_wrapper.py`, confirming the `BOT_SCRIPT` setting. It's crucial; any error here would be critical. I previously edited `src/main.py` using `default_api:edit`. Now I must check, is everything connected and correctly configured?\n\n\n**Validating Configuration Settings**\n\nI need to confirm the configuration settings in `src/agent_wrapper.py`. I'm verifying the `BOT_SCRIPT` setting; it should be set to `src/trading_bot.py`. I made some changes with the `default_api:edit` command to `src/main.py`. Now it is time to make sure that everything has been correctly connected.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771157368295_571","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/agent_wrapper.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":19092,"output":106,"cacheRead":15280,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19198,"cost":{"input":0.038183999999999996,"output":0.0012720000000000001,"cacheRead":0.003056,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.042512}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157362451}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b6ca4b6","parentId":"8996ab3b","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:09:28.318Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771157368295_571","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import sys\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport argparse\nimport signal\nimport time\n\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nBOT_SCRIPT = \"src/trading_bot.py\"\n\ndef is_running(pid):\n    \"\"\"Check if a process with the given PID is running.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Windows-specific check could be added here, but signal 0 is widely supported for existence check\n        # On Windows, os.kill with 0 is not supported in older versions, but usually fine in modern Python.\n        # Alternative: use tasklist\n        if os.name == 'nt':\n            # Use tasklist to check if PID exists\n            # Use errors='ignore' to handle potential non-UTF-8 output from localized Windows shell\n            output = subprocess.check_output(f'tasklist /FI \"PID eq {pid}\"', shell=True).decode(errors='ignore')\n            return str(pid) in output\n        else:\n            os.kill(pid, 0)\n            return True\n    except (OSError, subprocess.CalledProcessError):\n        return False\n\ndef start_bot():\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n            try:\n                pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                if is_running(pid):\n                    print(f\"Bot is already running (PID: {pid}).\")\n                    return\n                else:\n                    print(\"Found stale PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n            except ValueError:\n                print(\"Invalid PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n        \n        os.remove(PID_FILE)\n\n    print(\"Starting bot...\")\n    # Detached execution\n    if os.name == 'nt':\n        # Windows: specific flags to detach\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [sys.executable, BOT_SCRIPT],\n            creationflags=subprocess.CREATE_NEW_CONSOLE,\n            cwd=os.getcwd()\n        )\n    else:\n        # Unix\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            [sys.executable, BOT_SCRIPT],\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stdin=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            cwd=os.getcwd(),\n            start_new_session=True\n        )\n\n    with open(PID_FILE, 'w') as f:\n        f.write(str(process.pid))\n    \n    print(f\"Bot started with PID: {process.pid}\")\n\ndef stop_bot():\n    if not os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        print(\"Bot is not running (no PID file).\")\n        return\n\n    with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n        try:\n            pid = int(f.read().strip())\n        except ValueError:\n            print(\"Invalid PID file.\")\n            os.remove(PID_FILE)\n            return\n\n    if is_running(pid):\n        print(f\"Stopping bot (PID: {pid})...\")\n        try:\n            if os.name == 'nt':\n                subprocess.call(['taskkill', '/F', '/T', '/PID', str(pid)])\n            else:\n                os.kill(pid, signal.SIGTERM)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error stopping bot: {e}\")\n    else:\n        print(\"Bot process not found. Cleaning up PID file.\")\n\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        os.remove(PID_FILE)\n    print(\"Bot stopped.\")\n\ndef status_bot():\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n            content = f.read().strip()\n            # print(f\"DEBUG: Read '{content}'\")\n            try:\n                pid = int(content)\n                if is_running(pid):\n                    print(f\"STATUS: ACTIVE (PID: {pid})\")\n                    return\n                else:\n                    print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE (Stale PID file found)\")\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"STATUS: ERROR (Corrupted PID file): {e}\")\n    else:\n        print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Bot Control Interface\")\n    parser.add_argument('command', choices=['/start_bot', '/stop_bot', '/status'], help=\"Command to execute\")\n    \n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        parser.print_help()\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.command == '/start_bot':\n        start_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/stop_bot':\n        stop_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/status':\n        status_bot()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771157368317}}
