{"type":"message","id":"1e8692ef","parentId":"069f2c8c","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:09:52.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Assessing Application State**\n\nThe application builder seems to be functioning as expected given the versioning. Furthermore, the environment variables appear to be correctly configured. I've confirmed that the potentially problematic directory does not exist, and now I'll check for the existence of the critical primary script.\n\n\n**Refining the Verification Steps**\n\nI've moved on to verifying the bot's functionality. The code now confirms the existence of the expected primary script. Since the user was concerned about legacy handlers, I carefully checked `src/agent_wrapper.py` for any lingering Waxpeer-related code, which I didn't find. Finally, I will write a test script, `src/test_status.py`, to simulate the `/dm_status` command.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771157392321_574","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport sys\n\n# Mock paths\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nMASTER_PROTOCOL = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nEVOLUTION_LOG = \"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md\"\n\ndef test_status_logic():\n    print(\"Testing /dm_status logic...\\n\")\n    \n    status_msg = \"📊 **Bot Status Report**\\n\\n\"\n    \n    # 1. PID / Running State\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                pid = f.read().strip()\n            status_msg += f\"✅ **Status:** Active (PID: {pid})\\n\"\n        except:\n            status_msg += \"⚠️ **Status:** PID file error\\n\"\n    else:\n        status_msg += \"💤 **Status:** Inactive (No PID file)\\n\"\n\n    # 2. Master Protocol Version\n    version = \"Unknown\"\n    if os.path.exists(MASTER_PROTOCOL):\n        try:\n            with open(MASTER_PROTOCOL, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                content = f.read()\n                lines = content.splitlines()\n                for line in lines:\n                    if \"Version\" in line or \"v.\" in line.lower():\n                        version = line.strip()\n                        break\n                if version == \"Unknown\" and lines:\n                     version = lines[0].strip()\n        except Exception as e:\n             version = f\"Error: {e}\"\n    status_msg += f\"📜 **Protocol:** {version}\\n\"\n\n    # 3. Evolution Log (Last Change)\n    last_change = \"None\"\n    if os.path.exists(EVOLUTION_LOG):\n        try:\n             with open(EVOLUTION_LOG, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                lines = f.readlines()\n                # Get last non-empty line\n                for line in reversed(lines):\n                    if line.strip():\n                        last_change = line.strip()\n                        break\n        except:\n            pass\n    status_msg += f\"🧬 **Last Evolution:** {last_change}\\n\"\n    \n    # 4. LangFuse (Placeholder)\n    status_msg += \"🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\\n\"\n\n    print(\"--- GENERATED MESSAGE ---\")\n    print(status_msg)\n    print(\"-------------------------\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Create dummy PID for test\n    with open(PID_FILE, \"w\") as f:\n        f.write(\"12345\")\n    \n    test_status_logic()\n    \n    # Clean up\n    os.remove(PID_FILE)\n","file_path":"src/test_status.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":20955,"output":1060,"cacheRead":18580,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22015,"cost":{"input":0.041909999999999996,"output":0.01272,"cacheRead":0.003716,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.058345999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771157382030}}
