{"type":"message","id":"548ea26c","parentId":"e42673c4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:10:16.811Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reviewing the Implementation**\n\nI've just finalized the implementation, renaming and reorganizing some key files. I've switched the agent wrapper to now call the new `trading_bot.py`. A test script confirmed the updated logic is working as expected. Next, I'll review and fine-tune these recent adjustments to ensure optimal functionality.\n\n\n**Assessing Final State**\n\nI've successfully verified the system's final state. The `src/main.py` Telegram Bot, the renamed `trading_bot.py`, and the updated agent wrapper are all in place. The test script validation, along with the correct version of `python-telegram-bot` and the presence and readability of documentation files, confirms a successful integration. The menu setup in `post_init` is also confirmed.\n\n\n"},{"type":"text","text":"I have completed the Telegram Menu Upgrade for the DMarket HFT bot.\n\n### 🛠 Actions Taken:\n\n1.  **Replaced `src/main.py`:**\n    *   Created a new `src/main.py` using `python-telegram-bot` (v20+ `ApplicationBuilder`).\n    *   Implemented the following commands:\n        *   `/dm_start`: Starts the trading bot via `agent_wrapper.py`.\n        *   `/dm_stop`: Stops the trading bot via `agent_wrapper.py`.\n        *   `/dm_status`: Reports Bot PID, **Master Protocol Version**, **Last Evolution Log entry**, and LangFuse status.\n        *   `/dm_dashboard`: Returns the Streamlit dashboard URL.\n    *   **Menu Registration:** Added `post_init` hook to automatically register these commands with `set_my_commands` on startup.\n\n2.  **Migrated Trading Logic:**\n    *   Renamed the previous dummy `src/main.py` to `src/trading_bot.py`.\n    *   Updated `src/agent_wrapper.py` to point `BOT_SCRIPT` to the new `src/trading_bot.py`.\n\n3.  **Conflict Resolution:**\n    *   The new bot uses its own command handler and does not interfere with native OpenClaw gateway commands.\n    *   No legacy handlers (Waxpeer) were found in the active path, ensuring a clean slate.\n\n### 📊 Test Output (`/dm_status` Logic):\nBased on a local test of the status logic, the bot will output:\n```markdown\n📊 **Bot Status Report**\n\n✅ **Status:** Active (PID: 12345)\n📜 **Protocol:** **Version:** 1.0.0\n🧬 **Last Evolution:** *   **Rule:** \"No LLM calls in the hot path (HFT mode).\"\n🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\n```\n\n### 🚀 Next Steps:\n*   **Environment:** Ensure `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` is set in the environment before running `python src/main.py`.\n*   **Dashboard:** Set `STREAMLIT_URL` env var if the dashboard is hosted remotely (defaults to localhost:8501).","textSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":22718,"output":621,"cacheRead":21902,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23339,"cost":{"input":0.045436,"output":0.007452,"cacheRead":0.0043804000000000004,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0572684}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771157409230}}
